1. Implementation :
    -> extends Thread
    -> implements Runnable
2. The start() method is used to call the void run() method. When start() is called, a new stack is given to the thread, and run() is invoked to introduce a new thread in the program.

3. Thread States
    NEW  ----INTERRUPT----> DEAD
         ----START--------> RUNNABLE
    RUNNABLE ------RUN----> RUNNING
             ----INTERRUPT----> DEAD
    RUNNING -----WAIT------> BLOCKED
            -----SLEEP-----> BLOCKED
            -----INTERRUPT--> DEAD

